---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Felipe Sztutman — 100 Anos de Arte Moderna: a cena contemporânea"
  description="Print publication that dedicates a profile to Felipe Sztutman and links Cachoeira, sem título, para Mantiqueira, and OCEANVS within a single trajectory."
  lang="en"
  fullBleed={true}
  showHeader={false}
  showFooter={false}
  bodyClass="page-publicacao"
>
  <main class="text-page">
    <section class="text-entry">
      <div class="surface-links">
        <a href="/en/publicacoes" class="back">← publications</a>
        <a href="/en/#obras" class="surface-link">archive</a>
        <a href="/mapa" class="surface-link">relational map</a>
        <a href="/publicacoes/100-anos-de-arte-moderna" class="surface-link">PT</a>
      </div>
      <div class="text-type">print publication</div>
      <h1>100 Anos de Arte Moderna: a cena contemporânea</h1>
      <p class="text-subtitle">Editorial record that links Cachoeira, sem título, para Mantiqueira, and OCEANVS within a single trajectory.</p>
      <div class="text-date">Carlos Zibel Costa</div>
    </section>

    <article class="paper">
      <div class="body">
        <p>Within the site, this book matters less as press clipping and more as an institutional inscription of trajectory. It is not just a bibliographic mention: it is a dedicated profile of my work inside a publication that gathers artists from different generations and fields.</p>

        <p>The decisive element lies on <strong>pages 64–67</strong>, where the book articulates three moments that appear separately throughout the site: <em>Cachoeira</em> (2012), <em>sem título, para Mantiqueira</em> (2013), and <em>OCEANVS</em> (2022). This editorial montage makes legible a continuity between the <em>LUZCIDADE</em> series, digital fabrication, and the AYA phase of immersive exhibitions.</p>

        <p>There is also an important fold of lineage. The author is <strong>Carlos Zibel Costa</strong>, the same advisor who accompanied my thesis at FAU-USP. The editorial gesture closes an arc: what began as an academic investigation into light in space reappears years later as a recognizable artistic trajectory inside a printed publication.</p>

        <blockquote>
          <p>“New languages are not limited to new devices for personal use: they are capable of creating sensations necessary for the evolution of society. Technology as artistic manifestation builds the paths of art and the future.”</p>
          <footer>Antonio Curti, in the profile reproduced in the book</footer>
        </blockquote>

        <h2>Confirmed data from the photographed pages</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Title:</strong> <em>100 Anos de Arte Moderna: a cena contemporânea</em></li>
          <li><strong>Visible author / editorial organization:</strong> Carlos Zibel Costa</li>
          <li><strong>Cultural project:</strong> Instituto São Paulo de Arte e Cultura</li>
          <li><strong>Produced by:</strong> Instituto São Paulo de Arte e Cultura and Governo do Estado de São Paulo</li>
          <li><strong>Graphic design and cover:</strong> Cesar Mangiacavalli</li>
          <li><strong>Electronic editing:</strong> studio52</li>
          <li><strong>Pages with Felipe’s profile:</strong> 64–67</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Related works</h2>
        <div class="links-list">
          <a href="/en/obras/cachoeira">Cachoeira, para Córrego das Almas</a>
          <a href="/en/obras/mantiqueira">sem título, para Mantiqueira</a>
          <a href="/en/obras/oceanvs">OCEANVS</a>
          <a href="/en/sobre">About</a>
        </div>

        <h2>Circulation status</h2>
        <p>So far, the book has not been found in public online circulation. The information on this page derives from photographs of the physical copy. For that reason, the site does not republish the full content: it records the existence of the book, the place it occupies within the trajectory, and the editorial data confirmed so far.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>

<style is:global>
body.page-publicacao{background:#050505;color:#f1ece3}
body.page-publicacao a{text-decoration:none}
</style>

<style>
:root{--paper:#ece5d8;--ink:#111111;--line:rgba(17,17,17,.16);--muted:rgba(17,17,17,.58)}
.text-page{min-height:100vh;background:#050505}
.text-entry{padding:1.25rem 1rem 3rem;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08)}
.surface-links{display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:1rem}
.back,.surface-link,.text-type,.text-date{font:.72rem/1 var(--mono);letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase}
.back,.surface-link{display:inline-block;color:rgba(255,255,255,.55)}.back:hover,.surface-link:hover{color:#fff;text-decoration:none}.surface-link{color:rgba(255,255,255,.38)}
.text-type{color:rgba(255,255,255,.48);margin-bottom:.75rem}
.text-entry h1{font:900 clamp(2.4rem,7vw,6rem)/.92 var(--sans);letter-spacing:-.055em;margin-bottom:.85rem;max-width:15ch;color:#f1ece3}
.text-subtitle{max-width:48rem;font:1.05rem/1.65 var(--sans);color:rgba(255,255,255,.7);margin:0 0 .9rem}
.text-date{color:rgba(255,255,255,.42)}
.paper{background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);padding:1rem 1rem 3rem;min-height:56vh}
.body{font:1.05rem/1.85 Georgia,'Times New Roman',serif;max-width:780px;color:var(--ink)}
.body p{margin-bottom:1.35rem}.body h2{font:800 clamp(1.35rem,3vw,2rem)/1.1 var(--sans);letter-spacing:-.04em;margin:2.8rem 0 1rem;color:var(--ink)}
.body ul{padding-left:1.25rem;margin:0 0 1.35rem}.body li{margin:.35rem 0}.body em{color:rgba(17,17,17,.7)}.body strong{font-weight:700;color:var(--ink)}
blockquote{border-left:2px solid rgba(17,17,17,.28);padding-left:1rem;margin:1.75rem 0;color:rgba(17,17,17,.68);font-style:italic}blockquote footer{font:.72rem/1.5 var(--mono);letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
.links-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.55rem;font:.82rem/1.2 var(--mono);letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase}.links-list a{color:rgba(17,17,17,.72);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(17,17,17,.18);width:max-content}.links-list a:hover{color:#111;border-color:#111;text-decoration:none}
@media (min-width:900px){.text-entry,.paper{padding-left:2rem;padding-right:2rem}.text-entry{padding-top:1.5rem;padding-bottom:3.5rem}.paper{padding-bottom:4rem}.body{font-size:1.12rem}}
@media (max-width:720px){.text-entry h1{font-size:clamp(2.3rem,13vw,4rem)}.body{font-size:1rem;line-height:1.78}}
</style>
